NAME Crescent isle, beach
DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
REGION 11
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A stream once flowed down the beach at this point, shaping the sand into
narrow rivulets and tiny valleys. It has dried out with the passing of the
spring rains, of course, the salty air proving more thirsty than that on the
mainland despite its proximity to the crashing waves.
*DESCRIPTION_END
