NUMBER 3253
NAME Crescent isle, beach
DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
REGION 11
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The beach curves off to the north, forming the inner edge of the tiny
island, its white sands forming a sickle shape against the blue-green sea
water and the coarse, yellow grass which covers most areas not populated
with shrunken trees. A few blades of the tough vegetation have even made
their way out into the dry, hot sand itself, anchoring it slightly against
the wind and the water which conspire to erode it out of sight.
*DESCRIPTION_END
