ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A few clumps of damp sand have accumulated into dunes of a sort here, though
you can step over them without stretching your legs. Perhaps in a few seasons
they will have grown to the size of the hill to the south, but for now they
serve only as a windbreak for the waist-high brown and yellow grass.
*DESCRIPTION_END
