ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The north end of the island is a small, natural cove lined with the same
white sand which covers the rest of the area. A few small rocks protrude
from the water's edge, channeling the incoming waves away from the beach
and keeping the loose stuff from breaking up and collapsing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
