DARKNESS
CAVE
MINEC
REGION 11
MONSTER_GROUP 87
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cave splits in two as it heads southward, though from here you can see
that the split rejoins just a dozen or so paces on in a loop of sorts. An
outcropping of limestone forms a shallow, natural bowl in the south wall,
water trapped in it from the flowing of the walls slowly draining out of
it through a crack in the bottom.
*DESCRIPTION_END
